msContents.summary: Miscellany. The main text of the manuscript is King Magnus Eriksson's National Law of Sweden (Magnus Erikssons landslag), which ends defectively. There are also a number of shorter texts such as The Signs of the Zodiac about the signs of the zodiac and their effect on human undertakings, Calendar, The Importance of an Oath (Edens betydning), four lines of runic script and some notes in Swedish.

Schlyter and Collin, Corpus juris Sueo-Gotorum antiqui: Samling af Sweriges Gamla Lagar X 1-21:6, 51:10-338:9, 342-345:2, 364-367:9 Ed. L

condition.p: The manuscript has several defects, which have been noted throughout by Árni Magnússon; he has either inserted white paper leaves or written remarks in the bottom margin of the previous folio to indicate these defects. Fols 8r-9v are very stained and on fols 6 and 62 the bottom margins have been trimmed. There is a tear through the middle of fols 106r-111v. The notes on fol. 8r are almost illegible.

layout.p: There are rubrics, chapter numbers and running titles in red, while the initials are red or blue. Some of the running titles have been damaged during trimming.

additions.p: Judicial notes are written in the bottom margins of fols 22v and 49v.

origin.p: The manuscript was written in Sweden and dates to the second half of the fourteenth century.

custEvent.p: Restoration from 10 January until 23 February 1967. The manuscript was put on meeting guards and bound in a modern standard half binding.

surrogates.p:
